        'title'       => 'AIDA Formula: Attention, Interest, Desire, Action',
        'content'     => 'AIDA is the oldest and most reliable copywriting framework, and it maps perfectly to an e-commerce product page scroll. Attention: Open with a bold statement or question that stops the scroll. "Your feet deserve better than mass-produced insoles." This filters for the right audience and creates a micro-commitment to keep reading. Interest: Introduce the product with a fact, stat, or angle that makes the reader lean in. "The CloudStep Insole was developed with podiatrists and tested by 3,000 runners over 18 months." Interest is about credibility — you have their attention, now prove you are worth their time. Desire: Paint the outcome they want. "Imagine finishing a 10K without that familiar ache in your arches — just cushioned support from mile one to the finish line." Desire connects the product to the reader\'s life, not just their cart. Use sensory language: "memory foam that molds to your foot shape within minutes." Action: A single, clear CTA with a sweetener. "Add to Cart — backed by our 90-day comfort guarantee. If they do not change your run, send them back for free." Example full AIDA product description: Attention — "Tired of replacing your water bottle every three months?" Interest — "The ThermoFlask is built from surgical-grade stainless steel and keeps drinks cold for 24 hours or hot for 12 — verified by independent lab testing." Desire — "Picture ice-cold water at the end of a summer hike, straight from the bottle you packed that morning." Action — "Get yours today — free shipping and a lifetime warranty on every bottle."',
